Close Brace 5 Minute React: SublimeText

----------
References
----------
  Sublime Text Power User - Wes Bos: https://sublimetextbook.com/friend/CLOSEBRACE

---------
Shortcuts
---------
  Command Palette: CMD-SHIFT-P

  Select All Instances: CMD-CTRL-G

-----
Setup
-----
  Color Scheme used for TUT: Monokai

  Add Sublime to path so it can be executed from CMD:
    
    - open .bash_profile (or .zshrc) in home dir
      * .oh-my-zsh/custom/alias.zsh

    - add: alias subl="open -a /Applications/Sublime\ Text.app"

    - save & source file (source ~/.bash_profile)

    - install packages: Command Palette > "install package"
      + babel: Syntax definitions for ES6 Javascript with REact JSX Extensions
          (includes highlighting for ES7)
      + sass: Sass support for Textmat and Sublime Text
      + SublimeLinter
      + elsint: SublimeLinter-contrib-eslint v1.10.0

  




